query: অস্ট্রেলীয় ক্রিকেটার ডেভিড অ্যান্ড্রু ওয়ার্নার কবে জন্মগ্রহণ করেন ?

passage_en: David Andrew Warner (; born 27 October 1986) is a legendary Australian cricketer born in Paddington, New South Wales. He has a reputation as a very fast left-handed opening batsman. Also plays a role in wicket-keeping as needed by the team. David Warner is the first cricketer in Australia's 132-year cricket history to play in the national cricket team without any full experience of playing first-class cricket. He currently plays for New South Wales, Sunrisers Hyderabad and Sydney Thunder. David Warner was born in Paddington, a northern suburb of Sydney, New South Wales. query: আচেহ সালতানাতের তৃতীয় সুলতান কে ছিলেন ?
query_translated_en: Who was the third Sultan of Aceh Sultanate? [b]
passage_in_language: সুলতান সালাহউদ্দিন (মৃত্যু 25 নভেম্বর 1548) ছিলেন আচেহ-এর দ্বিতীয় সুলতান, 1530 থেকে 1530 সাল পর্যন্ত রাজত্ব করেছিলেন। 1537 বা 1539। তিনি আচেহের ক্ষমতার প্রতিষ্ঠাতা সুলতান আলী মুগায়াত স্যাহ-এর জ্যেষ্ঠ পুত্র ছিলেন। তার উচ্চাকাঙ্ক্ষী ছোট ভাই আলাউদ্দিন আল-কাহার দ্বারা প্রতিস্থাপিত হওয়ার আগে তিনি একটি সংক্ষিপ্ত এবং দুর্বল শাসনের নেতৃত্ব দেন। ১৫৩০ সালের আগস্টে সালাহউদ্দিন তার পিতার মৃত্যুর পর তার উত্তরাধিকারী হন। সুলতান আলি মুগায়ার সায়াকে তার স্ত্রী সিত্ত হুর বিষ প্রয়োগ করে বলে অভিযোগ, কিন্তু সালাহউদ্দিন এর সাথে জড়িত থাকার কোন ইঙ্গিত পাওয়া যায় না। "হিকায়াত আচেহ" এর মতে, তার মায়ের সরকারে শক্ত হাত ছিল।
passage_en: Sultan Salahuddin (died 25 November 1548) was the second sultan of Aceh, reigning from 1530 to c. 1537 or 1539. He was the eldest son of Sultan Ali Mughayat Syah, the founder of Aceh's power. He led a short and weak rule before being supplanted by his ambitious younger brother Alauddin al-Kahar. Salahuddin succeeded his father on the latter's death in August 1530. Sultan Ali Mughayar Syah was allegedly poisoned by his wife, Sitt Hur, but there is no indication of Salahuddin being involved in this. According to the "Hikayat Aceh", his mother had a strong hand in the government.

query: কত সালে আডলফ হিটলারের মূল ভাস্কর্যটি মাদাম তুসো জাদুঘরে উন্মোচন করা হয়েছিল ?
query_translated_en: In which year was the original sculpture of Adolf Hitler unveiled at Madame Tussauds? [b]
passage_in_language: ২০০৮ সালের জুলাই মাসে মাদাম তুসো জাদুঘরের বার্লিন শাখাটি বিব্রতকর ও বিরূপ পরিবেশের মুখোমুখি হয়। ৪১ বছর বয়সী একজন জার্মান ব্যক্তি দু'জন নিরাপত্তা প্রহরীকে এড়িয়ে আডলফ হিটলারের মোমের ভাস্কর্যটির ব্যাপক ক্ষতি করে। ধারণা করা হয় যে, নাৎসীবাদী জার্মানীর স্বৈরশাসক হিটলারের মূর্তির সাথে খ্যাতনামা খেলোয়াড়, চলচ্চিত্র তারকা এবং অন্যান্য ঐতিহাসিক ব্যক্তিদের অবস্থানের ফলেই এটি ঘটেছে। পরবর্তীকালে অবশ্য ভাস্কর্যটির মেরামত করা হয়। আডলফ হিটলারের মূল ভাস্কর্যটি এপ্রিল, ১৯৩৩ সালে লন্ডনের মাদাম তুসো জাদুঘরে উন্মোচন করা হয়। এরপর থেকে এ ভাস্কর্যটিও ধারাবাহিকভাবে ক্ষতিগ্রস্ত হয়। ফলে ১৯৩৬ সালে ভাস্কর্যটি পরিবর্তন ও মেরামত করতে বাধ্য হয় জাদুঘর কর্তৃপক্ষ। পরবর্তীতে নিরাপত্তা ব্যবস্থাকে আরও সুদৃঢ় করা হয়।
passage_en: In July 2008, the Berlin branch of Madame Tussauds faced an embarrassing and hostile environment. A 41-year-old German man eluded two security guards and caused extensive damage to a wax statue of Adolf Hitler. This is believed to be due to the placement of famous sportsmen, movie stars and other historical figures next to the statue of Hitler, the dictator of Nazi Germany. Later, however, the sculpture was repaired. The original sculpture of Adolf Hitler was unveiled at Madame Tussauds in London in April 1933. Since then, this sculpture has been continuously damaged. As a result, the museum authorities were forced to change and repair the sculpture in 1936. Later, the security system was strengthened.

passage_in_language: রাধাগোবিন্দ চন্দ্র (১৬ই জুলাই, ১৮৭৮, বাগচর গ্রাম, যশোর - ৩রা এপ্রিল, ১৯৭৫, দুর্গাপল্লী, বারাসাত) ভারত উপমহাদেশের সফলতম জ্যোতির্বিজ্ঞানীদের একজন। তিনি এ অঞ্চলে পর্যবেক্ষণমূলক জ্যোতির্বিজ্ঞান চর্চার দিক নির্দেশনা দিয়ে গেছেন। তার জন্ম তৎকালীন ভারতবর্ষের পূর্ববঙ্গে তথা বর্তমান বাংলাদেশে। রাধাগোবিন্দ ১৮৭৮ সালের জুলাই ১৬ তারিখে বর্তমান বাংলাদেশের যশোর সদর উপজেলার বকচর (বাগচর নামেও পরিচিত) গ্রামে জন্মগ্রহণ করেন। তার বাবা গোরাচাঁদ স্থানীয় একজন ডাক্তারের সহকারী ছিলেন, আর মা পদ্মামুখ ছিলেন একজন গৃহিণী। বকচর পাঠশালায় অধ্যয়ন শেষে রাধাগোবিন্দ যশোর জিলা স্কুলে পড়াশোনা করেন। কিন্তু লেখাপড়ার প্রতি তার তেমন আগ্রহ ছিলনা। বরং রাতের আকাশের প্রতি আকর্ষন ছিল বেশি। পড়াশোনায় অমনোযোগের কারণে তিন তিন বার প্রবেশিকা
passage_en: Radha Gobind Chandra (16 July 1878, Bagchar village, Jessore – 3 April 1975, Durgapalli, Barasat) was one of the most successful astronomers of the Indian subcontinent. passage_en: Mohenjodaro (Sindhi: मोहन जोड़ो मून जो डो) was one of the largest city-settlements of the Indus Civilization in ancient India. It is located in the Larkana district of the Sindh province of present-day Pakistan. Built around 2600 BC, it is one of the oldest cities in the world and a contemporary of the civilizations of ancient Egypt, Mesopotamia and Crete. The city's archaeological ruins are now a UNESCO World Heritage Site. It is also called "An Ancient Indus Metropolis". Mohenjodaro was built in 26th century BC. It was one of the largest cities of the ancient Indus Civilization, where another prehistoric city of Harappa was built. passage_en: Used in construction. The Indus Civilization (or Harappan Civilization) has its roots in the Mehergarh Civilization of 6000 BC. Harappa and Mohenjodaro, the two best cities of the Indus Civilization, were built around 2600 BC in the Indus Valley of the Punjab and Sindh region. These civilizations had written systems, urban centers, and social and economic diversity. In India too, several centers of this civilization have been discovered from the foothills of the Himalayas in eastern Punjab to Gujarat in the south. passage_en: Jagannath (meaning, "Nath of the World" or "Lord of the World") is a Hindu deity. He is worshiped in the Indian states of Odisha, Chhattisgarh (Bastar region), West Bengal, Jharkhand, Bihar, Assam, Manipur and Tripura and in Bangladesh. Jagannath is a special form of the Hindu god Vishnu or his avatar Krishna. He is worshiped along with his grandfather Balarama and sister Subhadra. Jagannath idols are usually made of wood. The eyes of this idol are big and round. The hand is incomplete. No legs are visible in the figure. The worship of Jagannath is also different from the worship of other Hindu deities. The main temple of Jagannath is located in the city of Puri in the state of Odisha. This temple is one of the Chardhams of Hinduism. There is no clear mention of Jagannath in the Vedas.

Geographically, the region lies in the Teesta-Torsha-Mahananda basin between the Darjeeling Himalayas in the north and the Gangetic plains in the south. Economically North Bengal is backward compared to South Bengal. However, the tourism industry in this region is very developed due to the beautiful natural environment. passage_en: Bartle Breese Bull or Bartle Bull III (born 1970) is an American writer, magazine editor and journalist specializing in foreign affairs and the Middle East. Bull is editor of the Middle East Monitor and foreign editor of "Prospect", a leading British political and cultural magazine. Bull is the son of Bartle Bull and Belinda Lawrence Breeese. His father was lawyer who graduated from Harvard College, where he was an editor of the "Harvard Crimson", Harvard University Law School and studied at Magdalen College, Oxford. His father was also the New York City coordinator of N.Y. Citizens for Kennedy in 1968.

passage_en: The wave equation is an important second-order linear partial differential equation for the description of waves—as they occur in classical physics—such as mechanical waves (e.g. water waves, sound waves and seismic waves) or light waves. It arises in fields like acoustics, electromagnetics, and fluid dynamics. Historically, the problem of a vibrating string such as that of a musical instrument was studied by Jean le Rond d'Alembert, Leonhard Euler, Daniel Bernoulli, and Joseph-Louis Lagrange. In 1746, d’Alembert discovered the one-dimensional wave equation, and within ten years Euler discovered the three-dimensional wave equation. The wave equation is a hyperbolic partial differential equation.

passage_en: Ramakrishna Paramahamsa (1836–1886) is a famous nineteenth-century Bengali mystic. Ramakrishna was a teacher of popular appeal, speaking in rustic Bengali with stories and parables. Key concepts in Ramakrishna's teachings included the oneness of existence and the unity and truth of all religions. Ramakrishna noted that God-realisation is the supreme goal of all living beings. passage_in_language: হড়প্পা (উর্দু/পাঞ্জাবি: , ) পাকিস্তানের পাঞ্জাব প্রদেশের একটি প্রত্নস্থল। এটি সাহিওয়াল থেকে ৩৫ কিলোমিটার পশ্চিমে অবস্থিত। প্রত্নস্থলটি রাভী নদী [ রাভি নদীর] পুরনো খাতের ধারে অবস্থিত একটি স্থানীয় গ্রামের নামাঙ্কিত। হরপ্পার বর্তমান গ্রামটি প্রত্নস্থল থেকে ৬ কিলোমিটার দূরে অবস্থিত। আধুনিক হরপ্পা ব্রিটিশ আমল থেকেই একটি ট্রেন স্টেশন। কিন্তু এটি একটি ছোটো পাকিস্তানি শহরমাত্র। প্রত্নস্থলে একটি প্রাচীন ব্রোঞ্জযুগীয় দুর্গশহরের ধ্বংসাবশেষ রয়েছে। এটি সেমেট্রি এইচ কালচার ও সিন্ধু সভ্যতার অংশ। মনে করা হয়, শহরটিতে ২৩,৫০০ মানুষ বসবাস করতেন। সেযুগের বিশ্বে এটি ছিল একটি বৃহৎ শহর। ব্রিটিশ আমলে প্রাচীন হরপ্পা শহরটি ভীষণভাবে ক্ষতিগ্রস্থ হয়েছিল। এই শহরের ধ্বংসাবশেষ থেকে ইঁট এনে তা লাহোর-মূলতান রেলপথ
passage_en: Harappa (Urdu/Punjabi: , ) is an archaeological site in the Punjab province of Pakistan. It is located 35 km west of Sahiwal. The site is named after a local village situated along the old channel of Ravi Nadi [Ravi River]. The present Harappan village is located 6 km from the ancient site. Modern Harappa has been a train station since the British period. But it is just a small Pakistani town. The site contains the ruins of an ancient Bronze Age citadel. It is part of Cemetary H Culture and Indus Civilization. It is believed that 23,500 people lived in the city. It was a major city in the world at that time. passage_en: Both claimed to be first heirs to the throne by descent. Duryodhana, who is younger than the elder Pandava Yudishti. Sage Kunti obtains a boon from Durvasa, allowing her to invoke any deity and bear her child. Out of curiosity, she decided to test the groom and chanting the mantra invoked the sun god and a child was handed over, Karna. Kunti, an unmarried mother, with a heavy heart floats Karna up the river Ganges, to avoid the embarrassment of having a child before marriage. After her marriage to Pandu, Kunti invoked other gods and had her sons, Yudhishthira, Bhima, Arjuna, Nakula and Sahadeva (from Madri).

passage_en: The 1977 Bogra mutiny was a mutiny in Bogra Cantonment on 30 September 1977. Ziaur Rahman was the chief of Army Staff, he served as the chief Martial law administrator after the Assassination of Sheikh Mujibur Rahman. Роспись её стен выполнили несколько художников итальянского Возрождения, наиболее ценимых в Италии конца XV века, в том числе Гирландайо, Перуджино и Боттичелли. В дальнейшем капелла была дополнена: при папе Юлии II — росписью потолка (Микеланджело, 1508—1512) и при папе Клименте VII — картиной Страшного Суда (Микеланджело, закончена в 1541). Композицию дополняли на нижнем уровне гобелены, из которых самые известные на сегодня создавались по рисункам Рафаэля (1515—1516).

Its walls were painted by several Italian Renaissance artists, most appreciated in Italy at the end of the 15th century, including Ghirlandaio, Perugino and Botticelli. Later, the chapel was supplemented: under Pope Julius II - with a ceiling painting (Michelangelo, 1508-1512) and under Pope Clement VII - with a painting of the Last Judgment (Michelangelo, completed in 1541). passage_en: Udayagiri (Udayagiri) is the largest Buddhist monastery in the state of Odisha. It houses the main stupa and Buddhist viharas. Along with the nearby Lalithagiri and Ratnagiri Buddharamas, it was also a part of the 7th century Pushpagiri Buddhist University. According to the inscriptions found here, the name of this place is "Madhavapura Mahaviharam". Research shows that this Buddhist Mahavihara was active from the 7th century to the 12th century. Udayagiri is situated in the foothills 90 km northeast of Odisha's capital Bhubaneswar and 70 km northeast of Cuttack city. Archaeological Survey of India since 1958 in this area

passage_in_language: కె. ఎం. మున్షీ (డిసెంబరు 30, 1887 - ఫిబ్రవరి 8, 1971) ఒక ప్రముఖ భారతీయ న్యాయవాది, రచయిత, మానవతావాది. కేంద్ర మాజీ వ్యవసాయ శాఖ మంత్రిగా పనిచేశారు. మున్షీ గుజరాత్ లో 1887డిసెంబర్ 30న బ్రోచ్ లో జన్మించారు. తండ్రి రెవెన్యూశాఖలో చిన్న ఉద్యోగం చేసేవాడు. తల్లి తాపీ బెహన్ ఇంట్లోనే ఉంటూ పిల్లలకు చదువు చెప్పేది. మున్షీ 15వ ఏట తండ్రి మానెక్ లాల్ చనిపోయాడు. ఇంటర్ వరకూ గుజరాత్ లో చదువుకున్న మున్షీ, డిగ్రీ కోసం ముంబై వచ్చాడు. 1905లో బీఏ, 1910లో ఎల్.ఎల్.బి పూర్తి చేశారు. అనంతరం ముంబైలో లాయర్ గా స్థిరపడ్డారు. మున్షీ తన 9వ ఏట నుంచే డైరీ రాసేవారు. రోజు భగవద్గీతలోని ఓ వ్యాక్యాన్ని ముందు రాసి, డైరీని మొదలు పెట్టేవారు. ఉత్తరాలు కూడా రాసే అలవాటుంది. స్నేహితులకు, బందువులకు ఉత్తరాలు రాస్తూ సలహాలు ఇస్తుండేవారు. వెర్ని వసూలత్, స్నేహసంభ్రమ,
passage_en: K. M. Munshi (December 30, 1887 – February 8, 1971) was an eminent Indian lawyer, writer and humanitarian. Former Union Minister of Agriculture. Munshi was born on December 30, 1887 in Broach, Gujarat. Father was doing a small job in revenue department. Mother Tapi Behan used to stay at home and teach the children. Father Manek Lal died when Munshi was 15. Munshi, who studied in Gujarat till Inter, came to Mumbai for his degree. BA in 1905 and LLB in 1910. Later settled as a lawyer in Mumbai. Munshi used to write a diary from the age of 9. They used to write a verse from Bhagavad Gita before the day and start the diary. He also used to write letters. query: యానాం యొక్క విస్తీర్ణం ఎంత ?
query_translated_en: What is the area of ​​Yanam?
passage_in_language: యానాం, పాండిచ్చేరి కేంద్రపాలిత ప్రాంతములోని ఒక జిల్లా మరియు ఆ జిల్లా యొక్క ముఖ్య పట్టణము. ఈ జిల్లా ఆంధ్ర ప్రదేశ్ లోని తూర్పు గోదావరి జిల్లాలో 30 చ.కి.మీ.ల విస్తీర్ణములో ఉంటుంది. ఇక్కడ నివసించే 32,000 జనాభాలో, చాలామంది తెలుగు మాట్లాడతారు. 1954 లో ఫ్రాన్స్ నుండి భారతదేశానికి ఇవ్వబడినా ఫ్రెంచి యానామ్ గా గుర్తింపు ఉంది. దీనికి 300 సంవత్సరాల చరిత్ర ఉంది. ఫ్రెంచి మరియు తెలుగు సంస్కృతుల మేళవింపు యానాంలో కనిపిస్తుంది. ఫ్రెంచి పరిపాలనలో జనవరిలో యానాం ప్రజల పండగ రోజులలో మంగళవారం సంత లో దొంగతనంగా దిగుమతి అయిన విదేశీ సరకు కొనటానికి తెలుగు వారు యానాం వెళ్లేవారు. ఇంతకు ముందు కళ్యాణపురం అనేవారు ఎందుకంటే బ్రిటీషు వారు 1929 లో శారదా చట్టం ద్వారా బాల్యవివాహాలు నిషేధించిన తర్వాత, ఇక్కడ ఆ పెళ్ళిల్లు జరిగేవి. 1936 లో యానాం జనాభా 5220. 1995-2005 అభివృద్ధి
passage_en: Yanam is a district in the Union Territory of Pondicherry and its chief town. This district covers an area of ​​30 sq km in East Godavari district of Andhra Pradesh. Of the 32,000 people who live here, most speak Telugu. It was given to India from France in 1954 but it is known as French Yanam. It has a history of 300 years. A fusion of French and Telugu cultures is seen in Yanam. During the French administration, the Telugu people used to go to Yanam to buy smuggled foreign goods on Tuesdays during the Yanam festival days in January. Earlier it was called Kalyanapuram because after the British outlawed child marriages through the Sarada Act in 1929, those marriages used to take place here. Population of Yanam in 1936 was 5220. query: విమానాన్ని ఎవరు కనుగొన్నారు?
query_translated_en: Who invented the airplane?
answers_translated_en: ['The Wright brothers', 'Wright brothers, Orville (August 19, 1871 – January 30, 1948) and Wilbur (April 16, 1867 – May 30, 1912)']
passage_in_language: రైట్ సోదరులు ఓర్విల్లే (1871 ఆగస్టు 19 - జనవరి 30, 1948) మరియు విల్బర్ (1867 ఏప్రిల్ 16 - మే 30, 1912) ఇద్దరు అమెరికన్ అన్నదమ్ములు, విమాన సృష్టికర్తలు, మరియు విమాన చోదక మార్గదర్శకులు. వీరు ప్రపంచపు మొట్టమొదటి భారీ యాంత్రిక విమానాన్ని కనిపెట్టి, నిర్మించి, నియంత్రించి 1903 డిసెంబరు 17 న విజయవంతంగా గాలిలో ఎగిరించారు. 1905 నుండి 1907 వరకు ఈ సోదరులు వారి ప్లయింగ్ యంత్రాన్ని మొదటి ఆచరణాత్మక స్థిర వింగ్ విమానముగా అభివృద్ధి పరచారు. ప్రయోగాత్మక విమానాలను తయారు చెయ్యడం మొదటిసారి కాకున్నా, రైట్ సోదరులు స్థిర వింగ్ ఆధారితంగా విమాన నియంత్రణను సాధ్యం చేయటం మొదట కనిపెట్టినదే.
passage_en: The Wright brothers Orville (1871 August 19 – January 30, 1948) and Wilbur (1867 April 16 – May 30, 1912) were two American brothers, inventors of airplanes, and aeronautical pioneers. They invented, built and controlled the world's first heavy mechanical airplane and successfully flew it on December 17, 1903. From 1905 to 1907 the brothers developed their flying machine into the first practical fixed wing aircraft. Although not the first to build experimental aircraft, the Wright brothers were the first to make fixed-wing based flight control possible.

passage_en: There was memory. Therefore, all human beings reform themselves and do pious deeds and enjoy the pleasures of heaven. As everyone enters heaven, the stampede in heaven is great. query: విస్తీర్ణం పరంగా ఆంధ్ర ప్రదేశ్ రాష్ట్రంలో అతి చిన్న జిల్లా ఏది?

passage_in_language: ఆంధ్ర ప్రదేశ్ రాష్ట్ర్రంలో 13 జిల్లాలు ఉన్నాయి. అనంతపురం జిల్లా అతి పెద్దది మరియు శ్రీకాకుళం జిల్లా అతిచిన్న జిల్లా. జిల్లాలను సాధారణముగా కోస్తాంధ్ర, రాయలసీమ ప్రాంతాలుగా విభజిస్తారు. కోస్తాంధ్రలో తూర్పు గోదావరి, పశ్చిమ గోదావరి, కృష్ణా, గుంటూరు, ప్రకాశం, శ్రీ పొట్టి శ్రీ రాములు నెల్లూరు, శ్రీకాకుళం, విజయనగరం, మరియు విశాఖపట్నంతో మొత్తం 9 జిల్లాలున్నాయి. రాయలసీమలో కర్నూలు, చిత్తూరు, వైఎస్ఆర్ కడప మరియు అనంతపురంతో 4 జిల్లాలున్నాయి.
passage_en: There are 13 districts in the state of Andhra Pradesh. Anantapur district is the largest and Srikakulam district is the smallest. The districts are generally divided into Coastal Andhra and Rayalaseema regions. Coastal Andhra has a total of 9 districts including East Godavari, West Godavari, Krishna, Guntur, Prakasam, Sri Potti Sri Ramulu Nellore, Srikakulam, Vijayanagaram, and Visakhapatnam. Rayalaseema has 4 districts namely Kurnool, Chittoor, YSR Cuddapah and Anantapur.

query: తమిళనాడులో రాష్ట్ర మొదటి ముఖ్యమంత్రి ఎవరు?
query_translated_en: Who was the first Chief Minister of Tamil Nadu?
passage_in_language: నాయకర్ నాయకత్వంలో ఇది 'ద్రవిడకజగం' పార్టీ అయ్యింది. ఇది రాజకీయ పార్టీ కాదు. స్వతంత్ర 'ద్రవిడనాడు' సాధన వారి లక్ష్యం. అప్పటి నాయకులు అన్నాదురై, పెరియార్ ల మధ్య విభేదాల కారణంగా ఈ పార్టీ రెండుగా చీలింది. అన్నాదురై నాయకత్వంలో 'ద్రవిడ మున్నేట్ర కజగం' (డి.యమ్.కె, DMK) పార్టీ 1956లో ఎన్నికలలోకి దిగింది. 1960 దశకంలో జరిగిన హిందీ వ్యతిరేక ఆందోళన సమయంలో డి.యమ్.కె బలం పుంజుకుంది. 1967లో కాంగ్రసును చిత్తుగా ఓడించి అధికారం కైవసం చేసుకుంది. 1969లో అన్నాదురై మరణించడంతో కరుణానిధి ముఖ్యమంత్రి అయ్యాడు. కరుణానిధి నాయకత్వంతో విభేదించిన సినీ నటుడు ఎమ్.జి.రామచంద్రన్ ( ఎమ్.జి.ఆర్, MGR)1972లో పార్టీనుండి విడిపోయి 'అఖిల భారత ద్రవిడ మున్నేట్ర కజగం' (AIADMK) స్థాపించాడు. 1977 నుండి 1987 వరకు ఎమ్.జి.ఆర్. ముఖ్యమంత్రిగా ఉన్నాడు. 1987లో ఎమ్.జి.ఆర్. మరణానంతరం పార్టీలో సంక్షోభం ఏర్పడింది. కాని ఎమ్.జి.ఆర్. భార్య జానకి రామచంద్రన్ నాయకత్వంలోని భాగం నిలబడలేకపోయింది.
passage_en: It became the 'Dravidakajagam' party under Naykar's leadership. It is not a political party. Their goal is to achieve an independent 'Dravidanadu'. The party split into two due to differences between the then leaders Annadurai and Periyar. Under the leadership of Annadurai, the 'Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam' (DMK) party contested the elections in 1956. DMK gained strength during the anti-Hindi agitation of the 1960s. In 1967, it defeated the Congress and took power. After Annadurai's death in 1969, Karunanidhi became the Chief Minister. Film actor MG Ramachandran (MGR), who disagreed with Karunanidhi's leadership, broke away from the party in 1972 and founded the 'Akhil Bharat Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam' (AIADMK).
